headline: Morgan Stanley Sustainable Signals: New Survey Shows Institutional Investors Expect Continued Growth in Sustainable Investing
summary: NEW YORK, December 03, 2024--Most institutional investors expect assets in sustainable funds to grow in the next two years, according to a new "Sustainable Signals" report by the Morgan Stanley Institute for Sustainable Investing. The survey, which polled more than 900 institutional investors across North America, Europe and Asia Pacific in July and August 2024, assesses attitudes of asset owners and asset managers toward sustainable investing, as well as emerging trends in the space.
